vectorData.altText: That's right! ‘A’ is the superior cervical ganglion. The ganglion contain postganglionic sympathetic neuronal cell bodies. The fibres that arise from it form the carotid plexus and provide sympathetic innervation to targets in the face. Note that the ganglion is medial to the internal carotid artery.

Identify the SCM muscle, then locate and trace the accessory nerve.
